wikipedia_page.main: Luke Robert David Strong  (born 7 December 1993) is a British trampoline gymnast. Strong won bronze at the 2014 European Championships.Strong nearly lost his leg in 2009 when he sustained a severe injury during a training session. Strong has made a full recovery and in the trials for the 2012 London Olympics, he missed out by 0.1 of a point. However, in 2014 Strong became the first British male senior trampoline gymnast to win a medal at a European championships in the last 32 years, winning bronze in Portugal.
